Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_proto_design_mode(25.10)                      get_proto_design_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_proto_design_mode   -   Returns   information   about  a  specified
       set_proto_design_mode parameter in the Innovus log file and the console

Syntax
       get_proto_design_mode

       [-help]

       [-effort]

       [-cover_fixed_macros]

       [-flexmodel_constraint_type]

       [-keep_guide]

       [-place_macro]

       [-remove_overlap]

       [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Returns information about a specified  set_proto_design_mode  parameter
       in  the  Innovus log file and the console. The following information is
       returned:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

              * Type (Boolean, string, and so on)

              * Whether the current value was set by user

       If you do not specify a parameter, the Innovus software returns  values
       for all of the set_proto_design_mode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each get_proto_design_mode parameter. For a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command: man get_proto_design_mode

       <parameter_names>
              Returns  information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See set_proto_design_mode for description of parameters.

Examples
              * The following command  returns  the  current  setting  of  all
                proto_design modes:

                get_proto_design_mode

Related Information
              *

                proto_design

              *

                set_proto_design_mode

              *

                Prototyping Methodologies chapter in the Innovus User Guide

